.SH NAME
dwc2_hsotg_send_reply \- send reply to control request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dwc2_hsotg_send_reply
.BI "(struct dwc2_hsotg *hsotg "  ","
.BI "struct dwc2_hsotg_ep *ep "  ","
.BI "void *buff "  ","
.BI "int length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hsotg" 12
The device state
.IP "ep" 12
Endpoint 0
.IP "buff" 12
Buffer for request
.IP "length" 12
Length of reply.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create a request and queue it on the given endpoint. This is useful as
an internal method of sending replies to certain control requests, etc.
